'''莱拉·特列季科夫'''（{{lang-ru|Лайла Третиков}}；{{lang-en|Lila Tretikov}}，{{bd|1978年|1月25日}}），又译'''莉拉·崔迪科夫'''，出生名'''奥尔加·“莉亚莉亚”·阿列克谢耶芙娜·特列季亚科娃'''（{{lang-ru|Ольга (Ляля) Алексеевна Третьякова}}），前[[维基媒体基金会|维基媒体基金会]]执行董事。生于[[蘇聯|蘇聯]][[莫斯科|莫斯科]]，十几岁时移居[[美国|美国]]，1999年起在[[加州|加州]]担任[[软件工程师|软件工程师]]，并且创立了一家技术营销公司，拥有数项联合软件专利。作为[[企业级软件|企业级软件]]专家，莱拉·特列季科夫曾经担任[[SugarCRM|SugarCRM]]公司的[[首席执行官|首席执行官]]兼工程副主席，直至2014年接任[[苏·加德纳|苏·加德纳]][[维基媒体基金会|维基媒体基金会]]首席执行官的职位。莱拉·特列季科夫因為[[搜尋引擎|搜尋引擎]] — [[維基百科知識引擎|維基百科知識引擎]] 開發和社群意見不同，以及過程中一度否認沒有此計劃等問題，已在2016年2月25日提出辭職<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://technews.tw/2016/02/26/wikimedia-foundation-head-is-forced-to-resign-due-to-community-distrust/ |title=維基基金會執行長因社群不信任而被迫辭職 2016/2/26 |accessdate=2016-03-01 |archive-date=2016-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160301001309/http://technews.tw/2016/02/26/wikimedia-foundation-head-is-forced-to-resign-due-to-community-distrust/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，會在3月31日生效<ref name=resignation2016>{{cite web | url=https://lists.wikimedia.org/pipermail/wikimedia-l/2016-February/082470.html | title=Thank you for our time together. | publisher=Lila Tretikov | date=25 February 2016 | accessdate=2016-03-01 | archive-date=2017-02-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170224121356/https://lists.wikimedia.org/pipermail/wikimedia-l/2016-February/082470.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 早年 ==
1978年1月25日，特列季科夫在[[莫斯科|莫斯科]]出生<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crunchbase.com/person/lila-tretikov |title=CrunchBase |publisher=CrunchBase |date= |accessdate=2014-05-10 |archive-date=2014-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502061412/http://www.crunchbase.com/person/lila-tretikov |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>[http://ria.ru/world/20140602/1010408517.html Wikimedia is headed by an American of Russian origin] {{Wayback|url=http://ria.ru/world/20140602/1010408517.html |date=20141227031437 }}. RIA Novosti</ref>，父亲是数学家，母亲是电影制片人<ref name=USAT>[http://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2012/11/27/women-engineers-facebook-yahoo-google-microsoft/1713835/ "Women band together, make inroads into tech"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2012/11/27/women-engineers-facebook-yahoo-google-microsoft/1713835/ |date=20150315011428 }} by Jon Swartz, ''[[USA_Today|USA Today]]'', 2012-11-27.</ref>。16岁她搬到纽约，在[[加州大学伯克利分校|加州大学伯克利分校]]勤工俭学，学习英语，赢得学位后离开<ref name=Seligman>{{cite web |last=Seligman |first=Katherine |title=The Woman To Run Wikipedia: Russian-born Former Cal Student Seen as "White Unicorn" |work=California Magazine |date=2014-05-09 |url=http://alumni.berkeley.edu/california-magazine/just-in/2014-05-13/woman-run-wikipedia-russian-born-former-cal-student-seen |accessdate=2014-08-21 |archive-date=2014-08-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140824061932/http://alumni.berkeley.edu/california-magazine/just-in/2014-05-13/woman-run-wikipedia-russian-born-former-cal-student-seen |dead-url=no }}</ref>。她学的是计算机科学和美术[[专业|专业]]，还研究[[机器学习|机器学习]]<ref name=Seligman/>。

== 生涯 ==
1999年，特列季科夫在[[升阳电脑|升阳电脑]]开启了她的职业生涯，担任升阳-网景联盟（Sun-Netscape Alliance）工程师，致力于[[Java|Java]]服务器。后来她创办了技术营销公司GrokDigital，而后被任命为[[SugarCRM|SugarCRM]]的首席信息官兼副总工程师<ref>[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=38550689&privcapId=11044816&previousCapId=11044816&previousTitle=SugarCRM,%20Inc. Executive Profile: Lila Tretikov] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6PFuykrDb?url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=38550689 |date=20140501230003 |dateformat=iso }} ''Bloomberg Businessweek'', 2014. Retrieved 2014-05-01. [https://www.webcitation.org/6PFuykrDb?url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=38550689%3Fhttp%3A%2F%2Finvesting.businessweek.com%2Fresearch%2Fstocks%2Fprivate%2Fperson.asp%3FpersonId%3D38550689 Archived here.]</ref>。

2012年，她获得史蒂夫大奖商业服务-11至2500名员工-计算机软硬件类年度女性执行官铜奖<ref name="2012 Stevie Awards">{{cite web |title=Stevie Awards For Women in Business: 2012 Stevie Award Winners |url=https://www.stevieawards.com/pubs/women/awards/414_2252_21756.cfm |work=stevieawards.com |location=Fairfax, VA |publisher=Stevie Awards, Inc |accessdate=2014-05-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115120515/http://www.stevieawards.com/pubs/women/awards/414_2252_21756.cfm |archive-date=2016-01-15 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

2014年5月，她接任了[[苏·加德纳|苏·加德纳]]在维基媒体基金会的执行董事职位<ref>[http://lists.wikimedia.org/pipermail/wikimediaannounce-l/2014-May/000905.html Please welcome Lila Tretikov, the Wikimedia Foundation's new ED] {{Wayback|url=http://lists.wikimedia.org/pipermail/wikimediaannounce-l/2014-May/000905.html |date=20140808144017 }} Jan-Bart de Vreede, Wikimedia Foundation Board of Trustees, 2014-05-01,</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Vreede|first=Jan-Bart de|title=Announcing our new Executive Director: Lila Tretikov|url=https://blog.wikimedia.org/2014/05/01/wmf_announces_new_ed_lila_tretikov/|work=Wikimedia blog|accessdate=2014-05-01|archive-date=2014-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140501201706/https://blog.wikimedia.org/2014/05/01/WMF_announces_new_ED_Lila_Tretikov/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Wikipedia's New Chief: From Soviet Union to World's Sixth-Largest Site|url=http://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2014/05/01/wikipedia-names-software-executive-tretikov-as-new-chief/|first=Jeff|last=Elder|publisher=Wall Street Journal|accessdate=2014-05-02|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303173701/http://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2014/05/01/wikipedia-names-software-executive-tretikov-as-new-chief/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Open-Source Software Specialist Selected as Executive Director of Wikipedia|last=Cohen|first=Noam|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/02/business/media/open-source-software-specialist-selected-as-executive-director-of-wikipedia.html|work=New York Times|accessdate=2014-05-02|archive-date=2014-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502081932/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/02/business/media/open-source-software-specialist-selected-as-executive-director-of-wikipedia.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，6月1日上任。特列季科夫的任命备受[[維基百科人|维基百科志愿者]]的争议，在任命之前，她仅编辑过维基百科一次{{efn|Kiss and Gibbs (2014) "She has taken flak from the online encyclopedia’s hardcore users for being an ‘amateur’ [...]"<ref name="theguardian-082014" />}}{{efn|Seligman (2014) "No, the new Wikipedian-in-chief does not write or edit entries on the world’s biggest collaborative encyclopedia."<ref name="calmag-2014">{{cite web |url=http://alumni.berkeley.edu/california-magazine/just-in/2014-05-13/woman-run-wikipedia-russian-born-former-cal-student-seen |title=The Woman To Run Wikipedia: Russian-born Former Cal Student Seen as "White Unicorn" |first=Katherine |last=Seligman |date=2014-05-13 |accessdate=2014-10-12 |publisher=California Magazine (UC Berkeley) |archive-date=2014-08-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140824061932/http://alumni.berkeley.edu/california-magazine/just-in/2014-05-13/woman-run-wikipedia-russian-born-former-cal-student-seen |dead-url=no }}</ref>}}{{efn|Seligman (2014) “I am not an editor,” said UC Berkeley grad Lila Tretikov [...] She did try to edit something seven years ago, she says, and like most of us she reads Wikipedia."<ref name="calmag-2014" />}}。她在智能数据映射和动态语言应用程序方面有多项共有专利<ref name="theguardian-082014">{{cite news|title=Wikipedia boss Lila Tretikov: 'Glasnost taught me much about freedom of information'|last=Kiss|first=Jemima|last2=Gibbs|first2=Samuel|url=http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/aug/06/wikipedia-lila-tretikov-glasnost-freedom-of-information|work=The Guardian|accessdate=2014-08-24|archive-date=2018-12-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226132738/https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/aug/06/wikipedia-lila-tretikov-glasnost-freedom-of-information|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=USPTO>{{cite web|title=Patent Search|url=http://search.uspto.gov/search?utf8=✓&affiliate=web-sdmg-uspto.gov&query=Lila+Tretikov%E2%80%8E&go=Go|publisher=United States Patent and Trademark Office|accessdate=2014-05-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029135948/https://search.uspto.gov/search?utf8=%E2%9C%93&affiliate=web-sdmg-uspto.gov&query=Lila+Tretikov%E2%80%8E&go=Go|archive-date=2019-10-29|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。她是[[OpenEd|OpenEd]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hart|first1=Michael|title=Wikimedia Foundation Director Named to OpenEd Board|url=http://thejournal.com/articles/2014/08/25/wikimedia-foundation-director-named-to-opened-board.aspx|work=THE Journal|date=2014-08-25|access-date=2015-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029135943/https://thejournal.com/articles/2014/08/25/wikimedia-foundation-director-named-to-opened-board.aspx|archive-date=2019-10-29|dead-url=yes}}</ref>和[[Rackspace|Rackspace]]公司的董事<ref>{{cite web|title=Rackspace Appoints Lila Tretikov to Board of Directors|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/pr/2204901|publisher=Digital Journal|date=2014-09-22|accessdate=2015-03-13|archive-date=2015-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716155923/http://www.digitaljournal.com/pr/2204901|dead-url=no}}</ref>，也是Zamurai公司的董事会顾问。

